library.description: Picard is a set of command line tools for manipulating high-throughput sequencing (HTS) data and formats such as SAM/BAM/CRAM and VCF. These file formats are defined in the Hts-specs repository. See especially the SAM specification and the VCF specification. Note that the information on this page is targeted at end-users. For developers, the source code, building instructions and implementation/development resources are available on GitHub. The Picard toolkit is open-source under the MIT license and free for all uses.

function.description: A set of command line tools (in Java) for manipulating high-throughput sequencing (HTS) data and formats such as SAM/BAM/CRAM and VCF.
